# Go Backend Standards

## Layering

```
Handler  → parse HTTP, validate input, format response
Service  → business logic, authorization checks, orchestration
db.Queries → SQL via sqlc only
```

Handlers must not call SQL directly. Services must not import `gin`.

## Package layout

One domain per folder: `internal/auth`, `internal/channels`, `internal/chat`, `internal/realtime`.

Wire dependencies in `cmd/api/main.go` only.

## Comments

- Package-level comment only when the package role is non-obvious.
- Comment exported functions when behavior or errors are not obvious.
- Do not narrate obvious code (`// increment counter`).

## Naming

- Handlers: `Register`, `Login`, `CreateChannel` — match route purpose.
- Services: verb + noun (`SaveMessage`, `GetChannels`).
- Errors: return `errors.New` or wrapped errors; handlers map to HTTP status.

## Realtime events

Use typed event names: `message.new`, `presence.online`. Document new events in `docs/WEBSOCKET_EVENTS.md` when that file exists.

